The bowl fucking breaks. You are not allowed ice cream for the rest of the week. You are a broken child, even though the layer of chocolate remains intact atop the mess you’ve made. Dejected, you reluctantly clean up your mess and go to bed.

The year is 2009. Your parents just brought home Breyers vanilla ice cream and a special kind of chocolate syrup. After dinner you have some of your ice cream, and without thinking, you grab the chocolate syrup. After pouring your usual gigantic amount of chocolate syrup on your ice cream, you notice something. You stab the layer of chocolate with your spoon but it will not break. You continue to stab the chocolate harder and harder, but it it is already too late. The chocolate molecules have formed a crystal lattice that cannot be broken by god himself. Your metal spoon bends in your hand as you attempt to force it down with all your might. Your parents are becoming concerned. They offer to microwave it for a few seconds, but you know that will ruin the ice cream. You are getting desperate. You run to your dad’s toolbox and grab a hammer. You run back and hit that layer of chocolate with all your might. It is no use.
